DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
Here defending the mouth of the wide Trazilar River stands a stout fortress,
one hundred and twenty foot square, with rough stone walls sixty feet tall.
The walls are surrounded by a moat. The road continues on toward the river
to the west.
*DESCRIPTION_END
