NUMBER 1654
NAME Houndsteeth Tower, Docks
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The docks are well protected by the fortress. Powerful seige engines line the
walls and a low sea wall protects the docks themselves. Across the river you
can see the low rolling hills that march off into the west. Boats dock here
to take you across the river.
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 33
EXIT E 1652
;-------------river boat---------
ITEM 6 1774
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 6
The riverboat docked here is the River Hawk. Paddle wheels on both sides push
the ship thru the water at a good clip. She has what looks like four decks,
the glassed in bridge at the top of the craft. A figurehead mounted on the bow-
post represents a flying hawk.  
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFITEM 5
        IFPREVERB GO 5
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER You make your way up the short gangplank onto the riverboat.
                ECHO OTHERS %N makes %h way up the short gangplank onto the riverboat.
                MOVE 2350
                AFFECT 2350
                ECHO OTHERS %N makes %h way up the short gangplank from the dock toward you.
                AFFECT 1654
        ENDIF
ENDIF
IFENTRY
    IFITEM 6
    	ECHO PLAYER As you approach the docks you notice a large river boat tied up there.
    ENDIF
ENDIF
