NUMBER 1653
NAME Houndsteeth Tower, Bailey
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
This large courtyard of the fortress is used for assembly by the troops and
also houses the stables for the garrisons horses. The crash of a smithy is
heard and the smell of baking bread also fills the air. Barrels of olive oil
line one side of the Bailey. A drawbridge leads out and a massive door leads
into the imposing keep.
*DESCRIPTION_END
